==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|treden|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|tredan||to tread, step on, trample, traverse, pass over, enter upon, roam through
|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|tredanan||trudanan|lang=en}}.  Cognate with Dutch {{term|treden}}, German {{term|treten}}, Danish {{term|træde}}, Swedish {{term|träda}}, Norwegian {{term|treda}}.

